race.comment: HAIIRO (8) ran well on debut last start to finish second over 1600m at Coleraine, beaten under a length. Sure to take a lot from that hitout and can land in a good spot from the draw. Go close. MISS MAVERICK (6) is a 12-start maiden who was fair at Murtoa last time out. Two minor placings prior have her in the mix. DON'T LOOK AWAY (5) is finding the breakthrough elusive, beaten 9 lengths into eighth at her latest appearance over 2000m at Warrnambool. Possible improver back in trip and in an easier race. No depth to the race at all. PRESTIGE GEOFFREY (9) has less convictions than most in this field.
